<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>#sets up the background info and meta data about the page, this is not loaded on the main body of the webpage 
	<meta charset="UTF-8"> #specifies the character encoding to Unicode for te html document
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width"> #specifies that the pizza wiki content should only be as wide as the display its showing on
<meta name="description" content="This is my new Wiki app" /> #useful for search engens, as it allows relevant serach queerys to be mached with the page.
<meta name="keywords" content="wiki, pizza, blog, memes"/> #also so useful for search engens, allows the page to show up when a search using the keywords is made
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" type="text/css" /> #adds a external style sheet, this allows the webpages to be more consistent in style, and makes updating style easier across webpages.
	<title>Pizza Wiki</title> # specifies that "Pizza Wiki" shows up in the browser tab
	</head>

<body>#loaded on teh main body of the webpage
<div class="main_container"></div># allows the following elements to be clumped together. 
<header>#represents a container
<b>Menu</b><br>
<a href="/">Home</a><br> #this and the following creates hyperlinks to the relevant webpages
<a href="/create">Create</a><br>
<a href="/about">About</a><br>
<a href="/edit">Edit</a><br>
</header>

<%= yield %> #This hands over the controls back to the erb, which this erb is embeded in.

<footer>#incerts content underneath all other content 
<p>Team Pizza</p>
</footer>
</body>
